[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":1736},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2022\u002F02\u002F11\u002Fgoogle-apps-script-sheets-as-rest-api\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2022\u002F02\u002F11\u002Fgoogle-apps-script-sheets-as-rest-api\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2022\u002F02\u002F11\u002Fgoogle-apps-script-sheets-as-rest-api\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2022\u002F02\u002F11\u002Fgoogle-apps-script-sheets-as-rest-api\u002F":1712,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2022\u002F02\u002F11\u002Fgoogle-apps-script-sheets-as-rest-api\u002F":1721},"\u002Fother\u002F20220211\u002F2705866340\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":1695,"date":1696,"description":1697,"extension":1698,"lang":1699,"meta":1700,"navigation":1324,"path":1701,"readingMinutes":1702,"seo":1703,"standalone":1704,"stem":1705,"tags":1706,"tldr":1709,"updated":1709,"url":1710,"__hash__":1711},"content\u002Fen\u002FMisc\u002Fgoogle-apps-script-sheets-as-rest-api.md","Use Google Apps Script + Google Sheets to Spin Up a Quick API","7058663402",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":1681},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,30,33,42,45,51,60,64,67,73,76,82,85,91,99,103,106,112,115,120,127,133,137,140,145,152,198,204,207,211,218,265,274,280,291,298,334,337,343,346,352,356,359,365,368,374,377,383,386,392,396,399,402,473,476,537,540,547,621,631,637,642,718,721,726,729,733,740,762,779,790,849,860,952,955,959,962,968,971,977,980,986,993,999,1002,1008,1011,1017,1027,1142,1149,1155,1158,1164,1167,1173,1177,1180,1276,1279,1575,1578,1648,1651,1655,1677],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"Sometimes you just need a quick API but don't want to spin up a whole backend — Koa, Express, Laravel, all overkill. Google Apps Script (GAS) is great for this. You can wire up GAS to Google Sheets, treat the sheet as a database, and have an API in 15 minutes.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"google-apps-script","Google Apps Script",[17,25,26],{},[27,28],"img",{"alt":23,"src":29},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002Fgoogle-apps-script\u002F1J6Qm1Gr3RaG1oVPW5v4-0Q.png",[17,31,32],{},"Google Apps Script is Google's scripting platform — lightweight, originally built to extend Google Sheets, so it pairs really well with Sheets specifically. Think of it as a tiny serverless backend that can do real work.",[17,34,35,36,41],{},"If you looked at the cover image, you'll notice GAS can do a lot. I've written about another GAS use case before — ",[37,38,40],"a",{"href":39},"\u002Fjavascript\u002F20190617\u002F3829122039\u002F","Using Google Apps Script to Solve CORS Issues (article in Mandarin)"," — but this post is just Sheets-as-API.",[17,43,44],{},"GAS has a really low learning curve, especially if you already know JavaScript — it uses web stack syntax: HTML, CSS, JavaScript.",[17,46,47],{},[27,48],{"alt":49,"src":50},"Uses standard web languages","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002Fgoogle-apps-script\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202022-02-11%2009.57.22.png",[17,52,53,54,59],{},"Let's try writing some ",[37,55,23],{"href":56,"rel":57},"https:\u002F\u002Fworkspace.google.com\u002Fproducts\u002Fapps-script\u002F",[58],"nofollow",".",[12,61,63],{"id":62},"create-a-sheet","Create a Sheet",[17,65,66],{},"First, create a Google Sheet. In Google Drive, right-click → Google Sheets:",[17,68,69],{},[27,70],{"alt":71,"src":72},"Create sheet","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002Fgoogle-apps-script\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202022-02-11%2010.00.03.png",[17,74,75],{},"Once created, rename it from the top so it's easier to find later:",[17,77,78],{},[27,79],{"alt":80,"src":81},"Rename","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002Fgoogle-apps-script\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202022-02-11%2010.01.15.png",[17,83,84],{},"You can use my sample data, or your own:",[17,86,87],{},[27,88],{"alt":89,"src":90},"Sheet content","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002Fgoogle-apps-script\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202022-02-11%2010.06.31.png",[17,92,93,94,98],{},"Save the sheet's URL — you'll need it shortly. Example: ",[95,96,97],"code",{},"https:\u002F\u002Fdocs.google.com\u002Fspreadsheets\u002Fd\u002F1MQPaKCV446eLXg2mDlLeKpsMc4nRnHDC7swlijAzkz0\u002Fedit#gid=0"," (sample URL, not a real sheet).",[12,100,102],{"id":101},"create-the-gas-project","Create the GAS project",[17,104,105],{},"Back in Google Drive, create a new Google Apps Script. It's tucked under \"More\":",[17,107,108],{},[27,109],{"alt":110,"src":111},"Create GAS","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002Fgoogle-apps-script\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96_2022-02-11_10_09_21.png",[17,113,114],{},"Rename it too — otherwise you'll lose track of which script is which. (Speaking from experience.)",[17,116,117],{},[27,118],{"alt":80,"src":119},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002Fgoogle-apps-script\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202022-02-11%2010.14.37.png",[17,121,122,123,126],{},"You'll land on the editor showing a ",[95,124,125],{},"myFunction"," boilerplate — that's where you write code:",[17,128,129],{},[27,130],{"alt":131,"src":132},"Editor","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002Fgoogle-apps-script\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202022-02-11%2010.15.22.png",[12,134,136],{"id":135},"getting-started-with-gas","Getting started with GAS",[17,138,139],{},"GAS uses standard web stack syntax — basically JavaScript.",[17,141,142],{},[27,143],{"alt":144,"src":50},"Web stack",[17,146,147,148,151],{},"You can declare variables and ",[95,149,150],{},"console.log"," just like normal JS:",[153,154,159],"pre",{"className":155,"code":156,"language":157,"meta":158,"style":158},"language-js shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","const myName = 'Ray';\nconsole.log(myName);\n","js","",[95,160,161,185],{"__ignoreMap":158},[162,163,166,170,174,177,181],"span",{"class":164,"line":165},"line",1,[162,167,169],{"class":168},"sWyjQ","const",[162,171,173],{"class":172},"sCcAr"," myName",[162,175,176],{"class":168}," =",[162,178,180],{"class":179},"sTRMh"," 'Ray'",[162,182,184],{"class":183},"sMAXC",";\n",[162,186,188,191,195],{"class":164,"line":187},2,[162,189,190],{"class":183},"console.",[162,192,194],{"class":193},"sj_SG","log",[162,196,197],{"class":183},"(myName);\n",[17,199,200],{},[27,201],{"alt":202,"src":203},"Writing Apps Script","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002Fgoogle-apps-script\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202022-02-11%2010.19.21.png",[17,205,206],{},"No extra learning curve. Onto the main thing — making Sheets behave like an API.",[12,208,210],{"id":209},"connect-to-the-sheet","Connect to the Sheet",[17,212,213,214,217],{},"GAS exposes ",[95,215,216],{},"SpreadsheetApp.openById"," to open a specific sheet by ID. Official example:",[153,219,221],{"className":155,"code":220,"language":157,"meta":158,"style":158},"var ss = SpreadsheetApp.openById(\"abc1234567\");\nLogger.log(ss.getName());\n",[95,222,223,249],{"__ignoreMap":158},[162,224,225,228,231,234,237,240,243,246],{"class":164,"line":165},[162,226,227],{"class":168},"var",[162,229,230],{"class":183}," ss ",[162,232,233],{"class":168},"=",[162,235,236],{"class":183}," SpreadsheetApp.",[162,238,239],{"class":193},"openById",[162,241,242],{"class":183},"(",[162,244,245],{"class":179},"\"abc1234567\"",[162,247,248],{"class":183},");\n",[162,250,251,254,256,259,262],{"class":164,"line":187},[162,252,253],{"class":183},"Logger.",[162,255,194],{"class":193},[162,257,258],{"class":183},"(ss.",[162,260,261],{"class":193},"getName",[162,263,264],{"class":183},"());\n",[17,266,242,267,270,271,273],{},[95,268,269],{},"Logger.log"," is GAS's logging — ",[95,272,150],{}," works too, both are supported.)",[17,275,276,277,279],{},"What goes into ",[95,278,239],{},"? The sheet ID. Pull it from the sheet URL:",[153,281,285],{"className":282,"code":283,"language":284,"meta":158,"style":158},"language-txt shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","https:\u002F\u002Fdocs.google.com\u002Fspreadsheets\u002Fd\u002F1MQPaKCV446eLXg2mDlLeKpsMc4nRnHDC7swlijAzkz0\u002Fedit#gid=0\n","txt",[95,286,287],{"__ignoreMap":158},[162,288,289],{"class":164,"line":165},[162,290,283],{},[17,292,293,294,297],{},"The ",[95,295,296],{},"1MQPaKCV446eLXg2mDlLeKpsMc4nRnHDC7swlijAzkz0"," part is the sheet ID. So:",[153,299,301],{"className":155,"code":300,"language":157,"meta":158,"style":158},"var ss = SpreadsheetApp.openById(\"1MQPaKCV446eLXg2mDlLeKpsMc4nRnHDC7swlijAzkz0\");\nLogger.log(ss.getName());\n",[95,302,303,322],{"__ignoreMap":158},[162,304,305,307,309,311,313,315,317,320],{"class":164,"line":165},[162,306,227],{"class":168},[162,308,230],{"class":183},[162,310,233],{"class":168},[162,312,236],{"class":183},[162,314,239],{"class":193},[162,316,242],{"class":183},[162,318,319],{"class":179},"\"1MQPaKCV446eLXg2mDlLeKpsMc4nRnHDC7swlijAzkz0\"",[162,321,248],{"class":183},[162,323,324,326,328,330,332],{"class":164,"line":187},[162,325,253],{"class":183},[162,327,194],{"class":193},[162,329,258],{"class":183},[162,331,261],{"class":193},[162,333,264],{"class":183},[17,335,336],{},"That hooks you into your sheet. Paste it into your GAS editor:",[17,338,339],{},[27,340],{"alt":341,"src":342},"Open sheet","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002Fgoogle-apps-script\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202022-02-11%2010.32.06.png",[17,344,345],{},"Click Run at the top.",[17,347,348],{},[27,349],{"alt":350,"src":351},"Run","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002Fgoogle-apps-script\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202022-02-11%2010.33.26.png",[12,353,355],{"id":354},"first-run-permission-flow","First-run permission flow",[17,357,358],{},"First run hits a permission prompt. Click Review permissions:",[17,360,361],{},[27,362],{"alt":363,"src":364},"Review permissions","h